enum.name: TpmManagerSecretStatus
enum.summary: The status of the sercrets that tpm manager hold. Each bit field presents the meanings listed below: 1. (0bX0000000): when the flag is set, the device uses TPM2. 2. (0b0XX00000): reserved. 3. (0b000X0000): has owner password. 4. (0b0000X000): has endorsement password (TPM2.0 only). 5. (0b00000X00): has lockout password (TPM2.0 only). 6. (0b000000X0): has owner delegate (TPM1.2 only). 7. (0b0000000X): has reset DA premissions.
